article.headline: Robert Morris 70, Iona 62
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. -- Jimmy Langhurst and Jeremy Chappell scored 17 points each, and Robert Morris held off a late-rallying Iona 70-62 Saturday night. Gary Wallace and Mezie Nwigwe added nine points each for the visiting Colonials (3-3). Gary Springer scored 17 points and Devon Clarke had 10 for the Gaels (2-3). Langhurst scored 11 points and Chappell eight to help the Colonials take a 30-17 lead at halftime. Robert Morris led by as much as 53-37 after Josiah Whitehead converted the first two free throws of the game for the Colonials with 8:46 left to play. Clarke's steal and subsequent 3-point play with 1:04 remaining capped an 11-3 scoring run that cut Robert Morris' lead to 61-55. Kashif Pratt's 3-pointer with 31.6 seconds left trimmed the edge to 64-59, but the Gaels got no closer. The Colonials shot 64.9 percent from the field in the game to 40 percent for Iona.
